uralism and discussing how the book remains relevant to ongoing sinological arguments. An earlier article by Allan, with supporting evidence for this book's thesis, is included as an appendix.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aLegendsxChina. 0aLegendszChina. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Studies. 4aHistory : History. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846226440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438462264423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438462264/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles